<h4 id="openstax-astronomy-2e-chapters-1-4-30" class="library-entry"><a href="https://openstax.org/books/astronomy-2e" target="_blank" rel="noopener">OpenStax Astronomy 2e — Chapters 1, 4, 30</a></h4>
<p>Free textbook spine for U1. Read Chapter 1 (Science and the Universe: A Brief Tour) for scale + AU/light-year setup; Chapter 4 (Earth, Moon, Sky) for orbital mechanics basics; Chapter 30 (Life in the Universe) — ESPECIALLY Section 30.2 Astrobiology — for the habitable-zone and multi-criteria habitability treatment that directly aligns with the Goldilocks Report.</p>
<dl class="opvl">
  <dt>Origin</dt><dd>Rice University / OpenStax; authors Andrew Fraknoi, David Morrison, Sidney Wolff (practicing astronomers); peer-reviewed.</dd>
  <dt>Purpose</dt><dd>Free college-level astronomy textbook.</dd>
  <dt>Value</dt><dd>Section 30.2 covers the habitability framework in HS-readable prose with figures, including the habitable zone, atmospheric retention, biosignatures, and the limits of Earth-centric assumptions. Use as foundational reading BEFORE students draft the Goldilocks Report.</dd>
  <dt>Limitations</dt><dd>U.S. observational examples dominate; recent JWST exoplanet atmosphere results may be underrepresented (textbook last updated 2022) — supplement with current NASA press releases. AI-training restriction applies — see cross-cutting OpenStax entry. May read; may not upload to NotebookLM/Claude.</dd>
</dl>

